            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="37828036">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">1. As Samuel Johnson purportedly wrote, Ã¢&euro;&oelig;The true measure of a man is how he treats someone who can do him absolutely no good.
2. Research shows that as people gain power, they feel large and in charge: less constrained and freer to express their natural tendencies. As takers gain power, they pay less attention to how theyÃ¢&euro;&trade;re perceived by those below and next to them; they feel entitled to purs...</span>
